ABI Pushing for More Women Directors on Company Boards, FT Says

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-09-26T01:32:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/abi-pushing-for-more-women-directors-on-company-boards-ft-says.html
The  Association of British Insurers 
is urging companies to increase the number of female directors
on boards, the Financial Times reported, citing research.  The ABI is also encouraging the elimination of cliches from
annual reports and instead providing more useful and specific
details on their policies on widening the experience of boards
and appointing top management, the FT said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 John Simpson  at 
 jsimpson12@bloomberg.net  